<Page x:Class="Hospital.View.Doctor.ShortcutsView"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
      xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
      xmlns:local="clr-namespace:Hospital.View.Doctor"
      mc:Ignorable="d" 
      d:DesignHeight="450" d:DesignWidth="800"
      Title="ShortcutsView">

    <Grid>
        <TextBlock Margin="10,10,-10,10" FontSize="16px">
            Every button has a letter underlined which represents the shortcut key for using it. <LineBreak/>
            ALT key to select the menu bar. <LineBreak/>
            Tab and SHIFT+Tab switches between inputs and buttons. <LineBreak/>
            Enter activates the selected item. <LineBreak/>
            Delete key to remove the selected item. <LineBreak/>
            Arrow keys navigate items in lists. <LineBreak/>
            CTRL+Tab and CTRL+SHIFT+Tab switches between tabs. <LineBreak/>
            Backspace or CTRL+B returns you to the previous window. <LineBreak/>
        </TextBlock>
    </Grid>
</Page>
